canonical:
  title: 鎭靜祭
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 坤德居中雖含弘而養物土行王季恐發洩以爲災玆薦吉蠲用圖禳禬宜借丕臨之便俾膺大競之休
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 鎭靜祭
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 坤德居中。雖含弘而養物。土行王季。恐發洩以爲災。玆薦吉蠲。用圖禳禬。宜借丕臨之便。俾膺大競之休。
korean:
  title: 진정제
  author: 김극기
  language: kor
  text: 땅의 덕은 중정(中正)하니, 비록 모든 것을 포용하여 만물을 생육하고 있으나, 끝 달[季月]에 흙[土]을 다루면 기운을 발산하여 재앙이 될까 두려워합니다. 이에 깨끗하고 부정타지 아니한 것을 제물로 바치어, 재앙을 제거하는 기도와 푸닥거리를 시도하오니, 마땅히 크게 강림하는 이편(利便)을 빌려서 원대하게 강성한 아름다움을 받게 하소서.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1130_020_0050&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Ritual for Calming the Earth
  author: Kim Geuk-gi
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The virtue of Earth dwells in perfect balance—
    though it embraces all and nourishes the ten thousand things,
    when we approach the final moon and handle what is earthen,
    we fear its qi will surge forth and bring calamity.

    So we present offerings pure and unsullied,
    offering prayers to ward off disaster and misfortune.
    We beseech the great descent of your benevolence,
    that we might receive the blessings of your boundless strength.
  footnotes:
    - The 'final moon' (季月) refers to the last month of each season, particularly the 12th lunar month, when earth-related activities were considered especially potent and dangerous in traditional East Asian cosmology.
    - This appears to be a ritual prayer or dedicatory text, likely presented before or during a ceremony intended to appease earth deities and prevent natural disasters.
